article.headline: Radford 82, Charleston Southern 53
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Artsiom Parakhouski scored 19 points and had 14 rebounds in Radford's 82-53 win over Charleston Southern on Monday night. The victory was the fourth straight and the fifth consecutive Big South win for the Highlanders (8-9, 5-1), marking the best start to the Big South season since beginning the 1999-2000 slate 6-0. The Highlanders started the game on a 13-1 run, led by six points from Parakhouski. Radford led by as many as 22 points, when Parakhouski put the Highlanders ahead 53-31 with 16:12 to play. Parakhouski, tied for No. 16 in the nation in rebounds heading into the game (10.2), led Radford in a 37-29 rebounding margin over the Buccaneers (5-10, 1-4). Kenny Thomas chipped in 18 points and Joey Lynch-Flohr added 15 for the Highlanders. Kelvin Martin, Jamarco Warren and Omar Carter each had 12 points for Charleston Southern, which lost its seventh straight.
